      • createNewInstance

        public ProcessDefinitionBuilderExt createNewInstance​(String name,
                                                     String version)
        Description copied from class: ProcessDefinitionBuilder
        Initiates the building of a new DesignProcessDefinition with the given name and version. This method is the entry point of this builder. It must be called before any other method. The DesignProcessDefinition building will be completed when the method ProcessDefinitionBuilder.done() or ProcessDefinitionBuilder.getProcess() is called.
        Overrides:
        createNewInstance in class ProcessDefinitionBuilder
        Parameters:
        name - the process name
        version - the process version
        Returns:
        this builder. Its ID is ZERO, as it is not deployed yet.
